### Observation 1: Recognize pre-approved autonomous specifications

**Status:** ACTIONED (2026-07-20) — Applied to brainstorming (weekly review)
**Date:** 2026-07-20
**Session context:** Implementing one ordered task from an existing approved specification in an unattended loop.
**Skill:** brainstorming
**Type:** open-source
**Phase/Area:** Approval gate and transition to implementation

**Issue:** The skill requires fresh questions, a duplicate design document, a commit, and another user approval even when the user has already approved an exact repository specification and explicitly instructed the agent to proceed autonomously without pausing.

**Suggested improvement:** Add a preflight branch that recognizes an explicit implementation request against an existing accepted design as approval. Require a brief scope and test-seam summary, then transition directly to the existing plan while preserving any user prohibition on commits.

**Principle:** Workflow gates should recognize equivalent evidence already supplied by the user so they preserve intent without duplicating approval rituals.

### Observation 2: Respect approved phase boundaries for schema validation

**Status:** ACTIONED (2026-07-20) — Applied to protobuf (weekly review)
**Date:** 2026-07-20
**Session context:** Defining fields-only Protobuf contracts in a phase that explicitly defers runtime invariants and pins the dependency set.
**Skill:** protobuf
**Type:** open-source
**Phase/Area:** Write Proto Code and Protovalidate requirement

**Issue:** The skill states that Protovalidate constraints are mandatory on every production field, but an approved phased specification may explicitly defer validation and prohibit adding unpinned dependencies. Following the skill literally would violate the source-of-truth contract and expand the current task.

**Suggested improvement:** Add a preflight check for approved schema phase boundaries and pinned dependencies. When validation is explicitly deferred, preserve the fields-only wire contract, record the deferral, and verify schema shape and Buf compatibility without introducing Protovalidate.

**Principle:** Implementation guidance should preserve approved phase boundaries and dependency constraints when the source of truth deliberately sequences structural contracts before validation.

